<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008</DATELINE><TITLE>A 'fly-by' killing with a primordial cellular weapon</TITLE><BODY>Autophagy has been suggested—on the basis of in vitro studies—to be involved in defense against bacterial challenge. A study in drosophila now shows the importance of autophagy in vivo and links a pattern recognition receptor to the autophagy pathway.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>